'''Ismaël Kenneth Jordan Koné''' (born June 16, 2002) is a professional [[Association football|soccer]] player who plays as a [[midfielder]] for [[Serie A]] club [[US Sassuolo Calcio|Sassuolo]]. Born in Ivory Coast, he plays for the [[Canada men's national soccer team|Canada national team]].

==Early life==
Koné was born in [[Abidjan]], Ivory Coast.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.lapresse.ca/sports/soccer/2021-08-13/le-cf-montreal-ajoute-le-jeune-ismael-kone-a-sa-formation.php|title=Le CF Montréal ajoute le jeune Ismaël Koné à sa formation|trans-title=CF Montreal adds young Ismaël Koné to its roster|date=August 13, 2021|work=La Presse|language=fr}}</ref> In 2010, he moved to Canada with his mother at age 7, growing up in Montreal.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.tvasports.ca/2021/09/07/ismael-kone-la-carte-cachee|trans-title=Ismaël Koné: The Hidden Map|title=Ismaël Koné: La Carte Cachée|first=Dave|last=Lévesque|date=September 7, 2021|work=[[TVA Sports]]|language=fr|access-date=2026-05-03}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.lapresse.ca/sports/soccer/2022-10-17/cf-montreal/ismael-kone-un-joueur-special.php|title=Ismaël Koné, un joueur " spécial "|trans-title=Ismaël Koné, a “special” player|language=fr|date=October 17, 2022|first=Jean-François|last=Téotonio|work=[[La Presse (Canadian newspaper)|La Presse]]|access-date=2026-05-03}}</ref> Two years later, he began playing youth soccer with the AS Notre-Dame-de-Grâce Panthers.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://journalmetro.com/local/saint-laurent/2782305/ancien-du-cs-saint-laurent-ismael-kone-fait-vibrer-stade-olympique/|title=Un ancien du CS Saint-Laurent fait vibrer le Stade olympique|language=fr|trans-title=A former CS Saint-Laurent rocks the Olympic Stadium|first=Olivier|last=Boivin|date=February 24, 2022|work=[[Métro (Montreal newspaper)|Journal Métro]]|access-date=2026-05-03}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.rds.ca/soccer/cfm/ismael-kone-la-proximite-de-l-echec-1.16369590|title=Ismaël Koné : la proximité de l'échec|trans-title=Ismaël Koné: the proximity of failure|language=fr|date=November 2, 2022|first=Nicolas|last=Landry|work=[[Réseau des sports|RDS]]|access-date=2026-05-03}}</ref> When he was 16, he joined [[CS Saint-Laurent]].<ref name="mlssign">{{Cite web|url=https://www.mlssoccer.com/news/cf-montreal-sign-midfielder-ismael-kone|title=CF Montréal sign midfielder Ismael Kone|date=August 13, 2021|first=Tom|last=Bogert|work=[[Major League Soccer]]|access-date=2026-05-03}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.cbc.ca/news/canada/montreal/isma%C3%ABk-kon%C3%A9-soccer-montreal-fifa-1.6585767|title=Montreal's Ismaël Koné bursts into soccer's global spotlight|first=Douglas|last=Gelevan|date=September 18, 2022|work=[[Canadian Broadcasting Corporation|CBC]]|access-date=2026-05-03}}</ref>

With CS Saint-Laurent he earned the bronze medal at the 2019 Canadian Under-17 Championship.<ref name="nugget" /> He went on trial in Belgium with [[K.R.C. Genk|Genk]] and [[Royal Excel Mouscron|Mouscron]],<ref name="mlssign" /> but was unable to sign with Mouscron as they did not have the funds available to sign a non-European player.<ref>{{Cite news |last=Kloke |first=Joshua |date=2022-12-01 |title=Canada’s Ismael Kone on the World Cup and his breakout year: ‘I don’t want to play like anyone else’ |url=https://www.nytimes.com/athletic/3836197/2022/11/14/ismael-kone-world-cup-platform-with-canada/ |access-date=2026-05-03 |work=The New York Times |language=en-US |issn=0362-4331}}</ref> Soon afterwards, he was forced to return to Canada due to the [[COVID-19 pandemic]], where he began training with [[CF Montreal U23]] and earned an invite to the [[CF Montreal|first team]]'s training camp in 2021.<ref name="nugget">{{Cite web|url=https://www.tvasports.ca/2021/08/12/la-prochaine-pepite-du-cf-montreal|trans-title=The Next "Nugget" of CF Montreal|language=fr|first=Emeric|last=Montminy|title=La Prochain "Pépite" du CF Montréal?|work=[[TVA Sports]]|date=August 12, 2021|access-date=2026-05-03}}</ref>

== Club career ==
===CF Montréal===
After a few months training with the [[CF Montréal]] first team, initially unable to sign a contract due to “some technicalities in MLS rules,”<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://nationalpost.com/pmn/sports-pmn/cf-montreal-sign-19-year-old-m-ismael-kone|title=CF Montreal sign 19-year-old M Ismael Kone|date=August 13, 2021|work=[[National Post]]}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.985fm.ca/nouvelles/sports/422063/soccer-ismael-kone-un-des-plus-beaux-espoirs-au-quebec|title=Ismaël Koné, " un des plus beaux espoirs au Québec "|first=Jeremy|last=Filosa|language=fr|trans-title=Ismaël Koné, "one of the most beautiful hopes in Quebec"|date=September 7, 2021|work=[[CHMP-FM|CHMP-FM 98.5 FM]]|access-date=March 19, 2022|archive-date=October 25, 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211025012725/https://www.985fm.ca/nouvelles/sports/422063/soccer-ismael-kone-un-des-plus-beaux-espoirs-au-quebec|url-status=dead}}</ref> Koné officially signed a two-year contract with two option years on August 13, 2021.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://en.cfmontreal.com/news/ismael-kone-signs-with-first-team|title=Ismaël Kone signs with first team|work=[[CF Montreal]]|date=August 13, 2021}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.journaldemontreal.com/2021/09/07/retenez-le-nom-dismael-kone|first=Dave|last=Lévesque|language=fr|date=September 7, 2021|trans-title=Remember the name of Ismaël Koné|title=Retenez le nom d'Ismaël Koné|work=[[Le Journal de Montréal]]|access-date=2026-05-03}}</ref> However, soon after signing his contract he suffered a knee injury, which limited his participation in training.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://lookcharms.com/ismael-kone-is-ready-to-come-and-lend-a-hand-to-cf-montreal/|title=Ismaël Koné is ready to come and lend a hand to CF Montreal|work=Look Charms|date=September 8, 2021|access-date=March 19, 2022|archive-date=October 21, 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221021160626/https://lookcharms.com/ismael-kone-is-ready-to-come-and-lend-a-hand-to-cf-montreal/|url-status=dead}}</ref>

After the 2021 season, he went to train with Montreal's sister club, Italian [[Serie A]] club [[Bologna F.C. 1909|Bologna]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://destroyandprogress.substack.com/p/who-is-ismael-kone-exploring-more?s=r|title=Who is Ismael Koné? A deep dive into the rapidly improving 19-year-old CF Montreal midfielder set to earn first CanMNT call-up this March window|date=March 18, 2022|first=Alexandre|last=Gangué-Ruzic|work=Destroy and Progress|access-date=2026-05-03}}</ref> Koné made his professional debut and scored his first goal with Montreal in a 3–0 win against [[Santos Laguna]] on February 23, 2022, in the [[2022 CONCACAF Champions League]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://btsvancity.com/2022/02/23/im-happy-with-the-result-cf-montreal-erases-santos-laguna-heartbreak-with-commanding-3-0-win-to-advance-to-champions-league-quarter-finals/|title="I'm happy with the result" CF Montreal erases Santos Laguna heartbreak with commanding 3–0 win to advance to Champions League quarter-finals|first=Alexandre|last=Gangué-Ruzic|date=February 23, 2022|work=BTS Van City|access-date=2026-05-03}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.tvasports.ca/2022/02/26/scenario-reve-pour-ismael-kone|title=Scénario rêvé pour Ismaël Koné|language=fr|first=Dave|last=Lévesque|work=[[TVA Sports]]|date=February 27, 2022 |trans-title=Dream scenario for Ismaël Koné|access-date=2026-05-03}}</ref> During the 2022 summer transfer window, [[English Championship]] clubs [[Sheffield United]] and [[Norwich City]] were reported to have approached Montréal over Koné's services.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.mlssoccer.com/news/cf-montreal-wunderkind-ismael-kone-seeks-great-leap-in-mls-cup-playoffs|title=CF Montréal wunderkind Ismaël Koné seeks great leap in MLS Cup Playoffs|first=Charles|last=Boehm|website=[[Major League Soccer]]|date=October 22, 2022|access-date=2026-05-03}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://journalmetro.com/local/saint-laurent/2897101/cf-montreal-ismael-kone-demeure-club/|title=CF Montréal: Ismaël Koné demeure avec le club|trans-title=CF Montreal: Ismaël Koné remains with the club|language=fr|date=September 2, 2022|first=Clément|last=Gaboury|work=[[Métro (Montreal newspaper)|Journal Métro]]|access-date=2026-05-03}}</ref>

===Watford===
In December 2022, English [[EFL Championship|Championship]] club [[Watford F.C.|Watford]] announced they had agreed to sign Koné on a transfer from CF Montréal, with the midfielder signing a four-and-a-half-year deal.<ref>{{cite web|title=Official: Hornets Sign Koné|date=December 5, 2022|url=https://www.watfordfc.com/news/official-hornets-sign-kone|work=[[Watford F.C.|Watford Football Club]]}}</ref> He made his debut on January 7, 2023, starting an [[FA Cup]] match against [[Reading F.C.|Reading]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.watfordobserver.co.uk/sport/23235429.watford-fa-cup-new-injury-concern/|title=Watford out of the FA Cup, but new injury is of more concern|date=January 7, 2022|work=[[Watford Observer]]|first=Andrew|last=French}}</ref> Koné scored his first goal for Watford in a 3–2 win over [[Norwich City F.C.|Norwich]] on November 28, 2023.<ref>{{Cite web |title='A moment of magic' {{!}} Ismael Kone pulls one back for Watford against Norwich |url=https://www.skysports.com/watch/video/sports/football/13018430/isma235l-kone-hits-a-rocket-as-watford-look-to-get-back-into-the-game |access-date=2023-11-29 |website=SkySports |language=en}}</ref> In June 2024, [[Olympique de Marseille|Marseille]] would announce that they had reached an agreement with Watford to sign Koné pending a medical, with Watford confirming that Koné would depart the club after appearing in 63 games and scoring 4 goals.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.om.fr/en/news/4808/club/89396-official-statement-om|title=Official Statement of OM|website=Olympique de Marseille|date=June 28, 2024}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.watfordfc.com/news/2024/june/28/official-kone-departs/|title=Koné Departs|website=Watford FC|date=June 28, 2024}}</ref>

=== Marseille ===
On June 28, 2024, it was announced [[Ligue 1]] club [[Olympique de Marseille|Olympique Marseille]] had reached an agreement for the permanent signing of Koné,<ref>{{Cite web |date=June 28, 2024 |title=Communiqué officiel de l'OM |url=https://www.om.fr/fr/actualites/4808/club/89393-communique-officiel-de-lom |access-date=June 30, 2024 |website=www.om.fr |publisher=Olympique de Marseille |language=fr|trans-title=Official press release from OM}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=2024-06-29 |title=Ismael Kone: Watford midfielder moves to Marseille |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/articles/c3grlj4er1go |access-date=2024-06-29 |website=BBC Sport |language=en-GB}}</ref> for a reported transfer fee of £15m including add-ons.<ref>{{Cite news |last=Leventhal |first=Adam |date=2024-06-30 |title=Marseille agree deal in principle with Watford for Canada midfielder Ismael Kone |url=https://www.nytimes.com/athletic/5592491/2024/06/26/ismael-kone-marseille-kone-transfer/ |access-date=2026-05-03 |work=The New York Times |language=en-US |issn=0362-4331}}</ref> After ankle injuries initially prevented him from practicing or playing regularly, Koné's time at Marseille became dominated by discussions of conflict between him and manager [[Roberto De Zerbi]].

On January 24, 2025, De Zerbi publicly stated that the player "hasn't shown me that he's capable of being part of this project," and indicated that he would likely leave the club.<ref>{{cite web |last=Scianitti |first=Matthew |url=https://www.tsn.ca/soccer/matthew-scianitti-kone-s-time-at-olympique-marseille-may-be-coming-to-a-messy-end-1.2241433 |title=Koné’s time at Olympique Marseille may be coming to a messy end |work=[[The Sports Network|TSN]] |date=January 24, 2025 |access-date= August 10, 2025 }}</ref> In August 2025, Marseille released a documentary account of its 2024–25 season that included footage of a training altercation between the two.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.tsn.ca/soccer/marseille-releases-video-of-confrontation-between-canmnt-s-ismael-kone-and-manager-roberto-de-zerbi-1.2342955 |title=Marseille releases video of Kone-De Zerbi bust-up |work=[[The Sports Network|TSN]] |date=August 5, 2025 |access-date= August 10, 2025 }}</ref>

==== Loan to Rennes ====
On February 3, 2025, Koné joined [[Stade Rennais FC|Rennes]] on loan for the remainder of the 2024–25 season.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.staderennais.com/actualites/mercato/ismael-kone-prete-par-lolympique-de-marseille |title=Ismaël Koné prêté par l’Olympique de Marseille |publisher=Stade Rennais FC |language=fr |date=3 February 2025 |trans-title=Ismaël Koné loaned out by Olympique de Marseille}}</ref> In the final match of the [[2024–25 Ligue 1|2024–25 Ligue 1 season]] at the [[Stade Vélodrome]], he scored a long-range goal from 30 meters against his parent club, Marseille.<ref>{{Cite web |title=La fête est totale ! - Débrief et NOTES des joueurs (OM 4-2 Rennes) |url=https://www.maxifoot.fr/football/article-61275.htm |access-date=2025-08-19 |website=www.maxifoot.fr |language=fr|trans-title=The celebration is complete! - Debrief and player RATINGS (OM 4-2 Rennes)}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |title=Marseille 4-2 Rennes (May 17, 2025) Final Score |url=https://www.espn.com/soccer/match/_/gameId/706726/stade-rennais-marseille |access-date=2025-08-19 |website=ESPN |language=en}}</ref>

=== Sassuolo ===
On July 29, 2025, amidst further media reports of incompatibility between Koné and De Zerbi, Koné was loaned to [[Serie A]] club [[US Sassuolo Calcio|Sassuolo]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Mercato : Ismaël Koné officiellement prêté par l'OM à Sassuolo |url=https://www.lequipe.fr/Football/Actualites/Mercato-ismael-kone-officiellement-prete-par-l-om-a-sassuolo/1581599 |publisher=L’Équipe |language=fr |date=July 29, 2025 |access-date=July 29, 2025|trans-title=Transfer market: Ismaël Koné officially loaned by OM to Sassuolo}}</ref> He made his official debut on August 15 in a [[Coppa Italia]] match against [[US Catanzaro 1929|US Catanzaro]], starting and playing 84 minutes in a 1–0 victory.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.sofascore.com/football/match/catanzaro-sassuolo/TfbsWfb |title=Sassuolo vs Catanzaro |website=Sofascore |access-date=September 8, 2025}}</ref> On February 2, 2026, Sassuolo made the transfer permanent.<ref>{{cite web|publisher=US Sassuolo Calcio|url=https://www.sassuolocalcio.it/prima-squadra/ismael-kone-acquisito-a-titolo-definitivo-dallolympique-marsiglia/|title=Ismael Konè acquisito a titolo definitivo dall’Olympique Marsiglia|trans-title=Ismael Konè has been acquired permanently from Olympique Marseille|date=February 2, 2026|access-date=February 2, 2026|language=it}}</ref>

On March 1, 2026, Koné scored the opening goal and was named man of the match in Sassuolo's 2–1 victory over [[Atalanta BC|Atalanta]], with the goal coming eight minutes after Sassuolo had been reduced to ten men.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Que |first=Brandon |date=2026-03-01 |title=WATCH: Man of the Match Ismael Kone delivers as Sassuolo overcome Atalanta after red card |url=https://canadiansoccerdaily.com/2026/03/01/watch-man-of-the-match-ismael-kone-delivers-as-sassuolo-overcome-atalanta-after-red-card/ |access-date=2026-05-01 |website=Canadian Soccer Daily |language=en}}</ref>

==International career==
[[File:Ismaël Koné WC2022 (cropped 2).jpg|thumb|Koné playing for [[Canada men's national soccer team|Canada]] at the [[2022 FIFA World Cup]]]]

Koné was eligible to play for [[Canada men's national soccer team|Canada]] and the [[Ivory Coast national football team|Ivory Coast]]. In March 2022, Koné was called up to Canada for their final window of [[2022 FIFA World Cup qualification – CONCACAF third round|2022 FIFA World Cup qualification]] matches.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Ismael Koné déjà appelé en équipe nationale |trans-title=Ismael Koné already called up for the national team |url=https://www.journaldequebec.com/2022/03/20/ismael-kone-deja-appele-en-equipe-nationale-1 |access-date=2026-05-03 |website=[[Le Journal de Québec]]}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last=Bedakian |first=Armen |date=March 20, 2022 |title='If you're good enough, you're old enough': CFMTL's Ismael Kone earns CanMNT call |url=https://onesoccer.ca/a/ismael-kone-dayne-st-clair-earn-canada-call-ups-cf-montreal-minnesota-united |access-date=2026-05-03 |website=[[OneSoccer]]}}</ref> He made his debut on March 24 against [[Costa Rica national football team|Costa Rica]], as a substitute for [[Jonathan Osorio]].<ref>{{Cite web |last=Jacques |first=John |date=2022-03-25 |title=Cautions Cost Canada In Cagey Costa Rica Clash |url=https://northerntribune.ca/world-cup-costa-rica-canada/ |access-date=2026-05-03 |website=Northern Tribune |language=en-US}}</ref>

Koné scored his first international goal for Canada in a friendly against [[Bahrain national football team|Bahrain]] on November 11, 2022.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.mlssoccer.com/news/ismael-kone-s-stock-is-rising-canada-draw-bahrain-in-world-cup-tune-up|title=Ismaël Koné's stock is rising: Canada draw Bahrain in World Cup tune-up|first=Peter|last=Galindo|work=[[Major League Soccer]]|date=November 11, 2022|access-date=2026-05-03}}</ref> Two days later on November 13, he was named to Canada's 26-man squad for the [[2022 FIFA World Cup]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://canpl.ca/article/canada-announces-26-man-squad-for-2022-fifa-world-cup-in-qatar|date=November 13, 2022|title=Canada announces 26-man squad for 2022 FIFA World Cup in Qatar|work=[[Canadian Premier League]]|first=Charlie|last=O'Connor-Clarke|access-date=2026-05-03}}</ref> He appeared in all three of the team's matches at the World Cup.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.mlssoccer.com/news/au-revoir-montreal-watford-bound-ismael-kone-seeks-biggest-leagues|title=Au revoir, Montréal: Watford-bound Ismaël Koné takes the next step|date=December 8, 2022|work=[[Major League Soccer]]|first=Tom|last=Bogert|access-date=2026-05-03}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.cbc.ca/sports/soccer/kone-grateful-cf-montreal-mls-1.6679542|title=Canadian international Koné 'grateful' to CF Montreal for giving him his start|date=December 8, 2022|work=[[CBC Sports]]|first=Elias|last=Grigoriadis|access-date=2026-05-03}}</ref> At the end of the year, Koné was named the men's 2022 [[Canada Soccer Young Player of the Year]].<ref name="young">{{Cite web |url=https://canadasoccer.com/news/simi-awujo-and-ismael-kone-named-canada-soccer-young-players-of-the-year/ |title=Simi Awujo and Ismaël Koné named Canada Soccer Young Players of the Year |date=December 20, 2022 |work=[[Canadian Soccer Association]]}}</ref> The following year, Koné was awarded again the Canada Soccer Young Player of the Year.<ref name="young2023">{{Cite web |url=https://canadasoccer.com/news/2023-ismael-kone-jade-rose-named-canada-soccer-young-players-of-the-year/ |title=ISMAËL KONÉ AND JADE ROSE NAMED CANADA SOCCER YOUNG PLAYERS OF THE YEAR |date=December 13, 2023 |work=[[Canadian Soccer Association]]}}</ref>

In June 2023, Koné was called up to Canada ahead of the [[2023 CONCACAF Nations League Finals]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Former CPLers Loturi, Zator called up by Canada for 2023 Concacaf Nations League Finals|date=June 7, 2023|url=https://canpl.ca/article/canada-canmnt-2023-concacaf-nations-league-final-roster|first=Mitchell|last=Tierney|work=[[Canadian Premier League]]|access-date=2026-05-03}}</ref> He scored in the [[Two-legged tie|second leg]] of the quarterfinals against [[Jamaica national football team|Jamaica]].

In June 2024, Koné was named to Canada's squad for the [[2024 Copa América]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://canadasoccer.com/news/canmnt-announce-2024-copa-america-roster/|title=CANMNT ANNOUNCE 2024 COPA AMÉRICA ROSTER|date=June 15, 2024|work= [[Canadian Soccer Association]]}}</ref> After starting in ''Les Rouges''' first two games, Koné was benched for [[Jonathan Osorio]] for the final group stage match—a 0–0 draw that sent Canada to the quarterfinals.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Canada 0-0 Chile (Jun 29, 2024) Team Stats |url=https://www.espn.com/soccer/matchstats/_/gameId/690722 |access-date=2024-11-29 |website=ESPN |language=en}}</ref>

== Style of play ==
Koné is a strong and willing dribbler who favors direct attacking runs, covers ground effortlessly, and maintains composure under pressure.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Aravena |first=Juan Pablo |date=2025-08-07 |title=Canadian Talent to Europe: Ismaël Koné & the Rise of CPL Soccer |url=https://blog.20bet.com/news/soccer/canadian-soccer-ismael-kone-cpl-europe/ |access-date=2025-08-19 |website=20bet Blog |language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last=calebmwilkins |date=2022-09-27 |title=Ismaël Koné – Player Report |url=https://targetscouting.com/2022/09/27/ismael-kone-player-report/ |access-date=2025-08-19 |website=Target Scouting |language=en-GB}}</ref>

During his loan at Stade Rennais, Koné showcased increased dynamism, aggression in duels, and effectiveness in breaking defensive lines, qualities that had been less evident at Olympique de Marseille.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Stade Rennais Mercato : Habib Beye bave sur un flop de l’OM |url=https://www.butfootballclub.fr/604843-stade-rennais-mercato-habib-beye-bave-sur-un-flop-de-lom/ |access-date=2025-08-19 |website=But! Football Club |language=fr|trans-title=Stade Rennais Transfer Market: Habib Beye gushes over an OM flop}}</ref> Head coach [[Habib Beye]] praised Koné, stating, "Ismaël is a player of immense quality."<ref>{{Cite web |title=" Ismaël Koné est un joueur d'une immense qualité " : Habib Beye encense le joueur prêté par l'OM |url=https://www.lequipe.fr/Football/Actualites/-ismael-kone-est-un-joueur-d-une-immense-qualite-habib-beye-encense-le-joueur-prete-par-l-om/1561927 |access-date=2025-08-19 |website=L'Équipe |language=fr|trans-title="Ismaël Koné is a player of immense quality": Habib Beye praises the player loaned out by OM}}</ref>

